      • guessPortTypesFromConnectedNodes

        public void guessPortTypesFromConnectedNodes(NodeAndBundleInformation nodeInfo,
                                             NodeSettingsRO additionalFactorySettings,
                                             ArrayList<FromFileNodeContainerPersistor.PersistorWithPortIndex> upstreamNodes,
                                             ArrayList<List<FromFileNodeContainerPersistor.PersistorWithPortIndex>> downstreamNodes)
        Called on single node persistors if their factory can't be loaded (extension not installed). They will check their up- and downstream nodes and guess their port types from. (Port types are defined in the node code, which is missing here).
        Specified by:
        guessPortTypesFromConnectedNodes in interface FromFileNodeContainerPersistor
        Parameters:
        nodeInfo - Info stored in xml
        additionalFactorySettings - possible settings for dynamic node factory (possibly null)
        upstreamNodes - The ordered list of upstream nodes, may contain null (not connected).
        downstreamNodes - the ordered list of downstream nodes (multiple connections to output possible). May contain null.

      • getDownstreamPortType

        public PortType getDownstreamPortType(int index)
        Used in FromFileNodeContainerPersistor.guessPortTypesFromConnectedNodes( NodeAndBundleInformation, NodeSettingsRO, ArrayList, ArrayList) to retrieve the port types of up- and downstream nodes. Might return null (if this node is missing, too).

        Downstream port types are input ports for SNC but output ports for WFMs.

        Specified by:
